original_question:
Given that point $P$ is any point on the circle $x^{2}+y^{2}=25$, a vertical line is drawn from $P$ to the $x$-axis, with the foot of the perpendicular being $H$. If $ \overrightarrow{MH}= \frac {3}{5} \overrightarrow{PH}$, and the locus of $M$ is curve $E$.

(1) Find the equation of $h(x)=f(x)-g(x)$;

(2) Suppose two chords $MN$ and $PQ$ pass through the left focus of curve $E$, with the slopes of the lines containing $MN$ and $PQ$ being $k_{1}$ and $k_{2}$ respectively. Determine whether $ \frac {1}{|MN|}+ \frac {1}{|PQ|}$ is a constant value. If it is, find this value; if not, explain why.

Present the answer in LaTex format: \boxed{Your answer}

